detailedReviews.text: This is a great BBQ shop. The food is fast and delicious. The service is good. The restaurant is clean. And there is usually enough seating to go around, even if it is busy.

detailedReviews.text: Great place.

detailedReviews.text: Absolutely delicious BBQ and friendly staff.

detailedReviews.text: Not my favorite BBQ spot in the area. Chicken and pulled pork are ok. Fries were soggy and undercooked and the brisket was hard.

detailedReviews.text: As you would expect for a BBQ place, it was extremely hot inside. I would have expected more fans or AC for guests but it was sweltering. I think the cost for what you get isn't quite fair for the consumer and it should be cheaper (or provide more meat). Service was average, nothing special but probably wont return.

detailedReviews.author: Dustin Baird
detailedReviews.text: I smoke my own meat so I'm pretty critical of BBQ places. I gotta say, everything at this place was amazing! Best ribs I've ever had and the mac and cheese was more and more delicious with every bite. Creamy and just peppery enough.

detailedReviews.author: Scott CTRL
detailedReviews.text:
Came here today with a coworker, it had probably been 3-4 years since I had been here. More than likely won‚Äôt ever be back. My portion of brisket was completely visually different than my coworkers (his were slices and mine was more shredded like left over bits and chunks) and mine had large hard bits of brisket that were very difficult to chew. Not appetizing. The garlic toast and mac n cheese were good, but nothing to write home about. The fries were a poor attempt at home cut fries, definitely missed the mark.
The Heirloom Restaurant group should be ashamed about the food that is being put out here and how expensive it is for such small portions. Shame on me for missing the up charge on brisket for the two meat plate, but they did have it displayed and had I seen it I definitely wouldn‚Äôt have got it. Find BBQ elsewhere. This isn‚Äôt it anymore.

detailedReviews.text: Five Star BBQ is awesome!  The food was very tasty -- especially the brisket and ribs.  But the best part was the live music.  Bill Brimley's band was playing and they crushed it!  Such a fun vibe and great music and even better food.  Can't wait to go back.

The coleslaw was decent, as were the beans and fries. I got a side salad which didn't come with salad dressing! We won't be returning.

Only downfall is that, probably because we arrived one hour before closing time, they only had just enough staff to serve you at the counter as if you were at a fast-food restaurant.
I would come back during the day and eat here again!

I think it was choice grade? Prime beef is harder to get right now, so maybe that‚Äôs why. Chicken was spot on! Pulled pork was pretty good, too. And the peanut butter chocolate pudding is top notch! All in all, for Utah County BBQ, you can‚Äôt go wrong. Worth the money in my opinion.

detailedReviews.author: Daniel Ogden
detailedReviews.text:
I ordered 2 lbs of brisket and pulled pork to go. I asked when ordering if they included sauce or if I needed to go someplace and put put some in containers. They said they would include it and asked me what types of sauce I wanted. I asked again when they handed me the order if the sauce was in the bag and they said yes.

Get back to the house and I have a pound of some of the driest brisket ever cooked and ZERO sauce.

Worst $70 I've ever spent.

Their mac and cheese tastes like it came from a jail or elementary school.

detailedReviews.text:

Will return to be sure

detailedReviews.author: Dustin Barnhurst
detailedReviews.text: My family of 29 came on New Year‚Äôs Eve an hour before close and the service was great and the food was better!!! My wife had the mashed potatoes gone before I could get a picture!!!

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Brown
detailedReviews.text: DONT ORDER ONLINE FOR PICKUP‚Ä¶. This is probably my 4th or 5th time order online and every time 15-30 mins behind what the actual pickup time is!

detailedReviews.author: Colby Capps
detailedReviews.text: No mac 'n' cheese at 5:40pm, 6 employees standing around bragging to each other about how big their catering is, and none of them doing anything while I wonder what I'm supposed to do and where I go to pay. House made chips were extremely salty. 3 small ribs (that were filled with little bones), a handful of chicken, chips, and 2 fried funeral potatoes was a shocking $18.38.

detailedReviews.author: Alicia
detailedReviews.text:
Great BBQ for Utah. It was so busy and so felt like it was already being validated as a great BBQ place. They were out of some sides around 6:45pm on a Saturday though which was a bummer.
Service was fast with the guy cutting up the meats, after that, the girls doing the sides were mega slow. Kind of lame given the line was super long as a party of 20 walked in while we were there.
Creamed corn was meh. Mac n cheese so good. Cornbread, and regular bread also great.

detailedReviews.author: Whitney Staples
detailedReviews.text: So delicious! Everything was great. Mashed potatoes were particularly delicious as well as the smoked turkey, brisket and ribs. Coleslaw is tangy and very good

detailedReviews.author: Danny Crane
detailedReviews.text: You go to a barbecue place because you want delicious mouthwatering brisket. Instead, you get the driest piece of meat you‚Äôve ever had in your life. Meat that tastes like leather. Even drowning it in barbecue sauce wasn‚Äôt enough to save this disgusting brisket. I‚Äôve never had brisket that tasted so disgusting. The lady serving the food kept coughing and didn‚Äôt cover her mouth. If you‚Äôre thinking about trying this place, I wouldn‚Äôt. If they gave me another plate of brisket for free, I would just throw it in the garbage.

detailedReviews.author: Gary Lee Gammenthaler
detailedReviews.text:
Order taker was very friendly and helped us with our choices.  The meal of course was awesome.
Great BBQ we loved it!
5 Stars *****
5 Star BBQ

detailedReviews.text: This brisket was dangerously amazing also the Cajun sausage was really good some reason especially with fry sauce? Anyways the service was also amazing everyone was really nice. Overall best barbecue restaurant ever.

detailedReviews.author: Art Tkachenko
detailedReviews.text:
I ordered a pound of brisket with the side of mashed potato. I thought I will take half of it to go but it was so good I finished all of it.  Definitely 5-star BBQ. üçñ

detailedReviews.text: I hate to leave a negative review but I don‚Äôt think the food here is worth the price I had a sandwich and baked beans the sandwich was fair but the baked beans I would not have again they were nothing like bbq baked beans the prices are too high for the lower quality of food.
